Refining the influence map...
Influence_map: The notation [i -> j] means an agent at position [i] of the first rule/var has an influence to an agent at position [j] of the second rule/var.
Influence_map:Wake_up_map:rule(0):'' A(x[.]),E(t[.])->A(x[1]),E(t[1]) -> rule(4):'' A(x[_],y[_],z[.]),E(t[.])->A(x[_],y[_],z[1]),E(t[1])[0->0]
Influence_map:Wake_up_map:rule(0):'' A(x[.]),E(t[.])->A(x[1]),E(t[1]) -> rule(5):'' A(x[1]),E(t[1])->A(x[.]),E(t[.])[0->0];[1->1]
Influence_map:Wake_up_map:rule(1):'' A(y[.]),E(t[.])->A(y[1]),E(t[1]) -> rule(4):'' A(x[_],y[_],z[.]),E(t[.])->A(x[_],y[_],z[1]),E(t[1])[0->0]
Influence_map:Wake_up_map:rule(1):'' A(y[.]),E(t[.])->A(y[1]),E(t[1]) -> rule(6):'' A(y[1]),E(t[1])->A(y[.]),E(t[.])[0->0];[1->1]
